rComments: This course covered lots of materials about distributed systems. Although there are some hard coding-based lab assignments, it really helps me to learn how to use zookeeper and how to replicate logs among Server-Client models. Prof is funny and he is an expert in this area, and I dont think exams are hard.

The professors did a good job to convey the materials, and DS concepts are useful and gaining more and more popularity. Exams are not that hard with a lot of similar contents as pervious years. Overall, good lectures and topics.

Projects are a lot of work but counts for very little marks (20%) Tests, Assignments and Exams take up 80% So what that means is 80% of your marks comes from solving problems on paper But the instructor doesn't show you how to do that at all. He just reads his lecture slides. It doesn't seem like he comes prepared to lectures.
His labs are very vague and hard to understand, with a huge amount of work. He is also very monotone and it is hard to listen to his lectures.
Class isn't really useful... read the material / search online for stuff. Most of his slides seem to be from online, also reads off slides alot...
Good prof. Get ready to work like a mule in his course though

Prof Jacobsen is monotone! His lectures are very boring and he always reads directly from his slides. Most of the time his lecture ends with "But we've already taken care of this.", in reference to the project that we are given which is the entirety of the course. It was a good waste of an hour as we heard him ramble on.
Horrible... His lectures are incomprehensible.  He assumes that we all have experience in tons of programming languages and that we all program for fun during weekends/summer etc.

Lectures rarely give info that is needed for the course.  Talks about concepts, and assumes that everyone will have seen all of the necessary background material in their spare time.  Actually feel like I know less about the assignment after leaving his lectures.
I really liked this prof. He explained the concepts very well and while the assignments were tough they were marked VERY easily (as per most lab work in uoft engineering). OS is a great course.
his classes are sooo boring and he sux. i would say that the classes are good for sleeping, except that he yelled at me for falling asleep in his class.

There was such a huge gap between lecture material and Assignment #3, which was so difficult that nobody (absolutely nobody in the class) got it working.

Honestly, all this guy is good at is making me go to sleep.  He can't teach! .. his IDEARS are stupid.  What the hell was the system call assignment when this guy never taught us system calls.
